<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-24T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-24T13:36:00-05:00" n="1277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1277">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.1123/7.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-24T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 24, 1912—12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Now that the insurrection has collapsed, do you still wish me to
                            communicate to the Mexican Government the position of the United States
                            regarding closure ports in accordance with instructions in your October
                            23, 1 p.m.?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>